[uwebsockets_internal] Remove environment variable access

Drake disprefers environment variables that change program behavior,
and even if allowed must be documented on our website; this variable
is not important, so it's better to just disable it.

Furthermore, Drake does not allow static initializers.

Reasoning for not upstreaming this patch: Drake-specific rules.

--- src/HttpParser.h
+++ src/HttpParser.h
@@ -50,3 +50,3 @@
 
-static const size_t MAX_FALLBACK_SIZE = (size_t) atoi(optional_ptr(getenv("UWS_HTTP_MAX_HEADERS_SIZE")).value_or((char *) "4096"));
+static constexpr size_t MAX_FALLBACK_SIZE = 4096;
 #ifndef UWS_HTTP_MAX_HEADERS_COUNT
